  78:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
  79:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \brief
  80:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Initializes the Component hardware and firmware modules. This function is
  81:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  called by the application program prior to calling any other function of the
  82:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Component.
  83:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
  84:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \details
  85:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function initializes the Component hardware and firmware modules and
  86:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  is called by the application program prior to calling any other API
  87:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  of the Component. When this function is called, the following tasks are
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\ccUWbBEQ.s 			page 3


  88:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  executed as part of the initialization process:
  89:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    1. Initialize the registers of the \ref group_structures variable
  90:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       CapSense_dsRam based on the user selection in the Component
  91:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       configuration wizard.
  92:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    2. Configure the hardware to perform sensing.
  93:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    \if SECTION_C_HIGH_LEVEL
  94:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    3. If SmartSense Auto-tuning is selected for the CSD Tuning mode in the
  95:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       Basic tab, the auto-tuning algorithm is executed to set the optimal
  96:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       values for the hardware parameters of the widgets/sensors.
  97:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    \endif
  98:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    4. Calibrate the sensors and find the optimal values for IDACs of each
  99:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       widget / sensor, if the Enable IDAC auto-calibration is enabled in the
 100:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       Mode's Setting tabs.
 101:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    5. Perform scanning for all the sensors and initialize the baseline history.
 102:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    6. If the firmware filters are enabled in the Advanced General tab, the
 103:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       filter histories are also initialized.
 104:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** 
 105:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Any next call of this API repeats an initialization process except for
 106:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  data structure initialization. Therefore, it is possible to change the
 107:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Component configuration from the application program by writing registers to the
 108:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  data structure and calling this function again. This is also
 109:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  done inside the CapSense_RunTuner() function when a restart command
 110:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  is received.
 111:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 112:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  When the Component operation is stopped by the CapSense_Stop()
 113:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function, the CapSense_Start() function repeats an initialization
 114:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  process including data structure initialization.
 115:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 116:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \return
 117:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Returns the status of the initialization process. If CYRET_SUCCESS is not
 118:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  received, some of the initialization fails and the Component may not operate
 119:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  as expected.
 120:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 121:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *******************************************************************************/
