 234:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 235:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \brief
 236:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Stops the Component operation.
 237:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 238:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \details
 239:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function stops the Component operation, no sensor scanning can be
 240:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  executed when the Component is stopped. Once stopped, the hardware block may
 241:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  be reconfigured by the application program for any other special usage. The
 242:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Component operation can be resumed by calling the CapSense_Resume()
 243:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function or the Component can be reset by calling the
 244:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_Start() function.
 245:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 246:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function is called when no scanning is in progress.
 247:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  I.e. CapSense_IsBusy() returns a non-busy status.
 248:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 249:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \return
 250:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Returns the status of the stop process. If CYRET_SUCCESS is not received,
 251:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  the stop process fails and retries may be required.
 252:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 253:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *******************************************************************************/
