 516:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
 517:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 518:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \brief
 519:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Performs customized data processing on the selected widget.
 520:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 521:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \details
 522:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function performs data processes for the specified widget specified by
 523:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  the mode parameter. The execution order of the requested operations is from
 524:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  LSB to MSB of the mode parameter. For a different order, this API
 525:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  can be called multiple times with the required mode parameter.
 526:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 527:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function can be used with any of the available scan functions. This
 528:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function is called only after all the sensors in the specified widget are
 529:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  scanned. Calling this function multiple times with the same mode without
 530:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  sensor scanning causes unexpected behavior. This function ignores the value
 531:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  of the wdgtEnable register.
 532:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  \if SECTION_C_LOW_LEVEL
 533:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  The CapSense_PROCESS_CALC_NOISE and
 534:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_PROCESS_THRESHOLDS flags are supported by the CSD sensing
 535:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  method only when Auto-tuning mode is enabled.
 536:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  \endif
 537:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  The pipeline scan method (i.e. during scanning of a widget, processing
 538:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  of a previously scanned widget is performed) can be implemented using this
 539:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function and it may reduce the total scan/process time, increase the refresh
 540:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  rate and decrease the power consumption.
 541:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 542:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  If the Ballistic multiplier filter is enabled the Timestamp must be
 543:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  updated before calling this function using the
 544:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_IncrementGestureTimestamp() function.
