 721:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Performs customized data processing on the selected widget's sensor.
 722:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 723:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \details
 724:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function performs data processes for the specified sensor specified by
 725:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  the mode parameter. The execution order of the requested operations is from
 726:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  LSB to MSB of the mode parameter. For a different order, this
 727:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function can be called multiple times with the required mode parameter.
 728:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 729:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  This function can be used with any of the available scan functions. This
 730:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function is called only after a specified sensor in the widget is
 731:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  scanned. Calling this function multiple times with the same mode without
 732:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  sensor scanning causes unexpected behavior. This function ignores the value
 733:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  of the wdgtEnable register.
 734:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 735:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  \if SECTION_C_LOW_LEVEL
 736:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  The CapSense_PROCESS_CALC_NOISE and
 737:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_PROCESS_THRESHOLDS flags are supported by the CSD sensing
 738:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  method only when Auto-tuning mode is enabled.
 739:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  \endif
 740:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 741:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  The pipeline scan method (i.e. during scanning of a sensor, processing
 742:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  of a previously scanned sensor is performed) can be implemented using this
 743:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  function and it may reduce the total scan/process time, increase the refresh
 744:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  rate and decrease the power consumption.
 745:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 746:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  If the Self-test library is enabled, this function executes the baseline duplication
 747:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  test. Refer to CapSense_CheckBaselineDuplication() for details.
 748:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 749:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \param widgetId
 750:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the widget to process one of its sensors.
 751:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  A macro for the widget ID can be found in the
 752:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense Configuration header file defined as
 753:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
 754:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 755:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \param sensorId
 756:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the sensor within the widget to process it.
 757:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  A macro for the sensor ID within a specified widget can be found in the
 758:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense Configuration header file defined as
 759:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  CapSense_<WidgetName>_SNS<SensorNumber>_ID.
 760:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 761:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \param mode
 762:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  Specifies the type of the sensor processing that needs to be executed for the
 763:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *  specified sensor:
 764:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    1. Bits [31..5] - Reserved.
 765:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    2. Bits [4..0] - CapSense_PROCESS_ALL - Executes all the tasks.
 766:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    \if SECTION_C_LOW_LEVEL
 767:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    3. Bit [4] - CapSense_PROCESS_THRESHOLDS - Updates the thresholds (only
 768:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       in auto-tuning mode).
 769:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    4. Bit [3] - CapSense_PROCESS_CALC_NOISE - Calculates the noise (only
 770:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *       in auto-tuning mode).
 771:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    \endif
 772:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    5. Bit [2] - CapSense_PROCESS_DIFFCOUNTS - Updates the difference count.
 773:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    6. Bit [1] - CapSense_PROCESS_BASELINE - Updates the baseline.
 774:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *    7. Bit [0] - CapSense_PROCESS_FILTER - Runs the firmware filters.
 775:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** *
 776:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_Control.c **** * \return
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\ccUWbBEQ.s 			page 25


